******
[1] France: UN worker discharged from hospital
Date: Sun 23 Nov 2014
Source: Reuters [edited]
http://www.reuters.com/article/2014/11/23/us-health-ebola-france-idUSKCN0J70FR20141123


A U.N. health worker was discharged from a French hospital on Sun 23 Nov 2014 and left the country after recovering from Ebola, the French Health Ministry said in a statement. The U.N. worker, whose name and nationality have not been disclosed, had been flown to France from Sierra Leone and was in isolation at the Begin military hospital in the eastern Paris suburb of Saint-Mande.

