[4] Precautions

Africa: Ebola affects soccer's Africa Cup of Nations
--------------------------------------
22 Nov 2014 (LA Times) In the last 2 weeks, former African champion Morocco was expelled from the continent's most important tournament; Equatorial Guinea was reinstated after being kicked out for using an ineligible player in qualifying; and Cuba, which once sent combat troops to Africa, will now be sending doctors to combat Ebola at next year's [2015] Africa Cup of Nations... - more
http://www.latimes.com/sports/soccer/la-sp-soccer-baxter-20141123-story.html

--
USA: Ebola virus caused cancellation of "Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice" filming in Morocco
------------------------------------------
22 Nov 2014 (Techtimes): Warner Bros has chosen to film "Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice" in New Mexico instead of Morocco due to concerns over the deadly Ebola virus... - more
http://www.techtimes.com/articles/20751/20141122/ebola-virus-caused-cancellation-of-batman-v-superman-dawn-of-justice-filming-in-morocco.htm

[Morocco has not reported a case of Ebola, but it is a transit point for flights both north and south from West Africa. - Mod.JW]

